What are the use of the borders?
	border properties allow you to Specify the style, width, and color of an element's border.
how many CSS border-styles?
	border-styles are:
	1.dotted - defines a dotted border
	2.dashed - define a dashed border
	3.solid - Defines a solid border
	4.double - defines a double border
	5.groove - defines a 3D grooved border. the effect depend on the border-color values
	6.ridge - defines a 3D ridge border.the effect depend on the border-color values
	7.inset - defines a 3D inset border.The effect depends on the border-color values
	8.outet - define a 3D outset border .The effect depends on the border-color values
	9.none - define no border
	10.hidden - defines a hiffen border
What is use of border widths?
	It is used to specifie the width for borders.
	The width can be set as a specific size (in px, pt, cm, em, etc) or by using one of the three pre-defined values: thin, medium, or thick
	specific side:
	The border-width property can have from one to four values (for the top border, right border, bottom border, and the left border
What is the use of border color?
	The border-color property is used to set the color of the four borders.
	It uses the color from css.
	Specific Side Colors
	The border-color property can have from one to four values (for the top border, right border, bottom border, and the left border).

Border-sides

		specifies which side of border
		
		border-top-style
		border-left-style
		border-right-style
		border-bottom-style
		
Border Shorthand
		border-style, border-width, border-color


Border-Radius

	is used to add rounded corners to element
	border-radius
